thread.title_full: Despite crazy October, Mets still unlikely to re-sign Daniel Murphy, report says | NJ.com

author: Ryan Hatch | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
title: Despite crazy October, Mets still unlikely to re-sign Daniel Murphy, report says
text:
He's hit five home runs this postseason and might carry the Mets to a World Series, but soon-to-be second base free agent Daniel Murphy probably still won't be back with New York beyond 2015. (Unless, of course, it's with the other New York team .)
RELATED : Mets' Daniel Murphy called out for being anti-gay 'bigot' during incredible postseason run
Kristie Ackert of the New York Daily News wrote Monday morning that the Mets remain unlikely to sign Murphy after this season is up and so is his contract, citing a need to keep payroll at a certain level. (The Mets, as of now, have the 10th-highest payroll going into '16 and that's without a new contract for Murphy.)
"He's been great, really great," one source told the News, "but it changes nothing."
MORE : Mets' Daniel Murphy turned himself into postseason star but will Mets re-sign him?
Murphy, in seven games this postseason, is 10-for-28 (.357) with those five home runs and some nifty plays in the field. The Mets surely don't sit two games up on the Chicago Cubs in the National League Championship Series without him.
"This is a good group," Murphy said after Game 2's victory Sunday. "I think we're having a whole bunch of fun right now, and we're going to enjoy this win tonight, enjoy the day off tomorrow, and I'm very excited about having Jake go for Game 3 right now."
